Now I understand the full picture. One critical design point for PATCH: the spec's ASSUMPTION notes `UpdateFeature(FeatureRow)` would clobber phase/status — but `SaveFeature` (which calls `SaveFeatureData`) does an upsert of ALL scalar fields including current_phase/status/priority from the in-memory feature. So for PATCH, the safest approach: load feature, mutate only title/priority + set UpdatedAt, then `SaveFeature(f)` — this writes current_phase/status from the loaded state (unchanged) so no clobbering. This is cleaner than adding a new DB method. Document this decision.

